description: API and backend route standards
globs: ["src/routes/**/*.ts", "src/services/**/*.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---
# API Rules
- All API routes should be in src/routes/
- Use proper error handling with try/catch
- Return consistent error response format: { error: string, details?: any }
- Include error details in development mode (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development')
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Validate input parameters before processing
- Use proper HTTP status codes (200, 400, 500, etc.)
- Services should be in src/services/ and handle business logic
- Routes should delegate to services, not contain business logic
- Use Express Router for route organization